Offload initialization until after initialization completion

This change possibly fixes #64 by reordering the initialization phase of
the plugin to load the extension fully only after Xcode sends the
“finish launching” notification. Still unable to reproduce but should in
any case be a good change. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

Fall back to /usr/local/bin as default if GEM_PATH doesn’t resolve

The new default location for system installed pods is /usr/local/bin as
of OS X El Capitan. Added a fall back to check this location.

Add support for expansion of $GEM_HOME and $GEM_PATH env variables.

Expansion of $GEM_HOME, ${GEM_HOME}, $GEM_PATH, and ${GEM_PATH} has been
implemented. This includes support for rvm and project-specific settings
(usually specified with .ruby-gemset and .ruby-version files); initial
expansion, upon Xcode startup, will be global (or the default gemset).
This is an Xcode limitation. When selecting a Cocoapods menu option, the
project path is determined via the key window (a hack, but there is no
other way). When $GEM_PATH is specified, path components are extracted
and applied individually for command execution.

Add ability to parse GEM_HOME in custom GEM_PATH.

Unfortunatetly, this does not respect the per-project setting of
ruby version and gemset that can be specified in the following
project directory files:

- .ruby-gemset
- .ruby-version

Still working on that.
